build.description:
- "cargo" for native compilation on a matching runner; 
- "cross" for cross-compilation via the "cross" crate (typically Linux → { Linux, *BSD }); 
- "cargo-cross-toolchain" for stable cross-compilation via taiki-e/setup-cross-toolchain-action (Linux → tier-2 BSD/illumos with prebuilt std); 
- "cargo-build-std" for tier-3 cross-compilation via setup-cross-toolchain-action + nightly + -Z build-std (Linux → tier-3 BSD without prebuilt std); 
- "vm" for builds that run inside a target-OS VM (e.g. OpenBSD on a vmactions/openbsd-vm sidecar) and bypass the standard upload-assets matrix.
